{"title": "History Teacher's Magazine, Vol. I, No. 5, January 1910", "description": "\"The History Teacher\u2019s Magazine is devoted to the interests of teachers of History, Civics, and related subjects in the fields of Geography and Economics. It aims to bring to the teacher of these topics the latest news of his profession. It will describe recent methods of history teaching, and such experiments as may be tried by teachers in different parts of the country. It will keep the teacher in touch with the recent literature of history by giving an impartial judgment upon recent text-books. It will give announcements of meetings of Teachers\u2019 Associations and accounts of their work. Its columns being open to the questions and contributions of every history teacher, it will serve as a clearing-house of ideas and ideals in the profession of history teaching.\" From the first issue of History Teacher's Magazine. \n\nIn this issue of the magazine, the LibriVox recording omits a section containing an index of \"The Old South Leaflets.\" Refer to page 98 of the e-text for this index.", "duration": 10164, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18", "name": " Various"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/historyteacherjan1910_1903_librivox/history_teachers_magazine_1903.jpg", "copyright_year": "1910", "genres": ["History"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Sarah Jennings"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Sarah Jennings"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Sarah Jennings"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Introductory Course in History in Harvard College", "readers": [10526], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/historyteacherjan1910_1903_librivox/historyteacherjan1910_01_various_64kb.mp3", "duration": 665}, {"section": 2, "title": "Impressions of American History Teaching", "readers": [11715], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/historyteacherjan1910_1903_librivox/